.TH TERMCRAFT 6 "2026-05-06" "0.1.0" "Games"
.SH NAME
termcraft \- terminal-based 2D sandbox survival game
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B termcraft
.RI [ server | client | connect ]
.RI [ address ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B termcraft
is a terminal-based 2D sandbox survival game written in Rust,
inspired by the classic early-2012 block-survival gameplay loop.
.PP
Features include procedural Overworld, Nether, and End generation,
mining, placement, inventory, crafting, furnaces, brewing, boats, and
chests. Health, hunger, combat, weather, fluids, gravity blocks, crops,
and farming are present. Passive and hostile mobs, villages, dungeons,
strongholds, and Nether fortresses complete the experience.
.SH MODES
.TP
.B (no argument)
Start the game in local single-player mode.
.TP
.B server \fR[\fIbind_addr\fR]
Start a headless multiplayer TCP server. Default address: 127.0.0.1:25565.
.TP
.B client | connect \fR[\fIserver_addr\fR]
Connect to a multiplayer server. Default address: 127.0.0.1:25565.
.SH CONTROLS
.TP
.BR A / D ", arrow keys"
Move left / right.
.TP
.BR W / Up / Space
Jump or swim up.
.TP
.B X
Toggle sneak.
.TP
.B E
Open inventory.
.TP
.BR 1 \- 9
Hotbar slot selection.
.TP
.B Left Click
Mine block or attack entity.
.TP
.B Right Click
Place block or interact.
.TP
.B F
Explicit block-use fallback (if right-click is unreliable in your terminal).
.TP
.B O
Settings menu.
.TP
.BR Q / Esc
Close UI or quit from world view.
.SH FILES
Game saves are written to a
.B saves/
subdirectory relative to the current working directory.
.SH NOTES
This game is an unofficial fan project, not affiliated with Mojang or
Microsoft. Client/server multiplayer mode is experimental.
